andardized with 27 primary letters. This step made the writing system simpler, systematic, and ready for wider use in education and publication.</p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">2008 – Community Refinement</span></p><p>In 2008, community organizations contributed to further improvements. The script was adjusted to enhance readability and learning efficiency, ensuring it met modern educational needs.</p><h2>Structural Features of the Script</h2><p>Mundari Bani stands out because of its thoughtful and independent design.</p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Independent Origin</span></p><p>The script is original. It is not borrowed or adapted from other Indian writing systems.</p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">One Sound, One Letter</span></p><p>Each character corresponds clearly to a specific Mundari sound. This reduces confusion and maintains pronunciation accuracy.</p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Simple and Learnable</span></p><p>With 27 letters, the system is straightforward and suitable for learners of all ages.</p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Adaptable Format</span></p><p>The script functions effectively in handwriting, print, and digital formats.</p><h2><span style=\"color: rgb(45, 106, 79);\">Educational Transformation</span></h2><p>The introduction of Mundari Bani in schools across parts of Odisha marked a major turning point.</p><p>By the early 2000s:</p><p></p><ul><li>Children began learning in their mother tongue.</li><li>Textbooks were developed in Mundari.</li><li>Oral traditions were documented in written form.</li><li>Cultural pride among younger generations increased.</li></ul><p></p><p>The script became a foundation for stronger education and community confidence.</p><h2><span style=\"color: rgb(45, 106, 79);\">Digital Recognition and Unicode Inclusion</span></h2><p>A historic milestone occurred in 2021–2022 when Mundari Bani—also known as Nag Mundari—was added to the Unicode Standard.</p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Unicode Block: U+1E4D0–U+1E4FF</span></p><p>This inclusion allows the script to be used on:</p><p></p><ul><li>Computers</li><li>Smartphones</li><li>Websites</li><li>Digital archives</li><li>Academic platforms</li></ul><p></p><p>Unicode recognition ensures the script’s survival in the modern technological era.</p><h2><span style=\"color: rgb(45, 106, 79);\">Part of a Broader Indigenous Movement</span></h2><p>Mundari Bani stands alongside other indigenous scripts from eastern India, including:</p><p></p><ul><li>Ol Chiki</li><li>Warang Citi</li></ul><p></p><p>These scripts share a common goal: preserving tribal languages and strengthening cultural identity in the face of assimilation.</p><h2><span style=\"color: rgb(45, 106, 79);\">Present Status and Future Prospects</span></h2><p>Today, Mundari Bani continues to grow through:</p><p></p><ul><li>Academic research</li><li>Community initiatives</li><li>Digital integration</li><li>Educational programs</li></ul><p></p><p>While full institutional adoption remains an ongoing effort, the progress achieved so far is significant. From handwritten sketches to global digital recognition, the script’s journey reflects dedication and resilience.</p><h2><span style=\"color: rgb(45, 106, 79);\">Conclusion</span></h2><p>Mundari Bani is not merely a technical invention. It is a powerful expression of cultural survival and self-determination.</p><p>It captures the true sound of the Mundari language, strengthens education, and ensures relevance in the digital age. In an era where many indigenous languages face decline, Mundari Bani stands as a lasting example of how a script can become a symbol of hope, identity, and continuity.</p>"
